# LangRush — API Key Setup
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The API key is NO LONGER stored in a .env file.
# It is injected at build/run time using Flutter's --dart-define flag.
# This prevents the key from being bundled in the APK and extracted.
#
# ── How to run / build ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Debug (flutter run):
#   flutter run --dart-define=OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-your-key-here
#
# Release APK:
#   flutter build apk --release --dart-define=OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-your-key-here
#
# Release AAB (Play Store):
#   flutter build appbundle --release --dart-define=OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-your-key-here
#
# ── IDE configuration ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Android Studio → Run/Debug Configurations → Additional run args:
#   --dart-define=OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-your-key-here
#
# VS Code → .vscode/launch.json:
#   "args": ["--dart-define=OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-your-key-here"]
#   ⚠️  Make sure .vscode/launch.json is in .gitignore if it contains the key!
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your OpenAI API key at: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys

